Create a Data Graph from a Data Kit

Avoid the time involved in creating a data graph manually by using a data graph from a published data kit. You can deploy a data kit containing data graphs using an unmanaged package. Changes that you make to the original data graph don’t affect the data graph in the data kit.

From the App Launcher, search for and select Data Graphs.
Click New, and click Use a Data Kit.
Select a data kit.
Only published data kits are shown.
Select a data graph.
Only data graphs with a primary DMO that matches the data kit data graph's primary DMO are shown. If the data kit data graph’s primary DMO is a unified DMO, the DMO suffixes don’t have to match. For example, the data kit’s data graph has a primary DMO with the API name UnifiedIndividualR1, but only data graphs with the primary DMOs UnifiedIndividualR2 and UnifiedIndividualR3 exist. Then those two data graphs are shown.
Edit the properties of the new data graph.
The properties are prepopulated from the original data kit data graph.
Edit the data graph’s related objects and fields.
All the related objects and fields that the data graph references must exist in your org. If any don’t exist, you must create them or remove them from the data graph.
